				\begin{document}$$H^2$$\end{document}) values were higher for biometric and emergence traits (ranging from 0.75 for MTE to 0.99 for WF) compared to seedling growth traits (ranging from 0.22 for TDM to 0.32 for LA).

Most correlation estimates among the 13 evaluated traits were significant at 1%. In general, genetic correlations (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
