Correlation analysis alone can lead to misinterpretations due to indirect effects among explanatory traits. Path analysis was performed to partition the estimates of phenotypic correlations into direct and indirect effects. The analysis is presented in Fig. 5, illustrating the direct effects of explanatory variables on DQI and their correlations (top).Fig. 5
