We initially tested a total of 13 microsatellite markers, only eight yielded consistent and reliable amplification across all individuals analyzed. In this eight evaluated loci, a total of 118 alleles were identified. The number of alleles per locus ranged from 8 (EE43) to 20 (EE05), with an average number of alleles per locus (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
